4. Each person who entered Jamaica on or after March 18, 2020, shall forthwith contact
      the Ministry with responsibility for health and wellness, either—
         (a)      through the website https://jamcovid19.moh.gov.jm/ or e-mail covid19@moh.gov.jm;
                  or
         (b)      by calling any of the following numbers—
                       (i)     888-ONE-LOVE (888-663-5683);
                       (ii)    888-754-7792;
                       (iii)   876-542-5998;
                       (iv)    876-542-6007; or
                       (v)     876-542-6006,
      and shall provide to that Ministry the residential address where that person can be located,
      and all other information required by that Ministry for the purposes of measures to combat
      the risk of transmission of the SARS-CoV-2 (Coronavirus COVID-19).

6.—(1) During the period from April 8, 2020, to April 21, 2020—
           (a)     gatherings in any public place shall not exceed 10 persons at a time; and
           (b)     except as required for work in accordance with paragraph 7, each person at such
                   a gathering shall maintain a distance of at least 91.44 centimetres (or 3 feet) from
                   other persons.
                 (2) Sub-paragraph (1)(a) does not include—
           (a)     subject to sub-paragraphs (3) and (5), hospitals, infirmaries and nursing homes;
           (b)     security forces;
           (c)     services concerning the provision of health, water, electricity, sanitation,
                   firefighting, civil aviation, or telecommunications;
           (d)     correctional services;
           (e)     tourist establishments, as defined in the Public Health (Tourist Establishments)
                   Regulations, 2000;
           (f)     subject to sub-paragraph (4), retail services (such as markets, supermarkets,
                   pharmacies and “corner shops”) for the provision of food, medicine or other
                   necessities of life;
           (g)     sittings of the Houses of Parliament, and meetings of the Cabinet, or any
                   committees thereof;
           (h)     Ministries, Departments and Agencies of Government, and Municipal
                   Corporations;
           (i)     Tax Administration Jamaica, the Bank of Jamaica, the Jamaica Customs Agency,
                   the Office of Disaster Preparedness and Emergency Management and the
                   Independent Commission of Investigations;
           (j)     financial services, as defined in the Banking Services Act;
           (k)     credit union business by a society registered under the Co-operative Societies
                   Act;
           (l)     services connected with oil-refining and with the loading, distribution,
                   transportation or retail of petroleum fuel, liquefied natural gas or any renewable
                   energy source;
           (m)     services connected with the loading and unloading of ships and with the storage
                   and delivery of goods at, or from, docks, wharves and warehouses operated in
                   connection with docks or wharves;
352                   PROCLAMATIONS, RULES AND REGULATIONS                          [APRIL 8, 2020
            (n)   the provision of public transportation by bus (including buses operated by the
                  Jamaica Urban Transit Company or the Montego Bay Metro Company Limited),
                  limited to seated passengers only;
            (o)   the provision of public transportation by motor car, limited to one person less
                  than the maximum number of persons allowed to be carried under the relevant
                  licence;
            (p)   the Judiciary and persons employed to a court;
            (q)   Factories as defined in the Factories Act;
            (r)   any service, activity or public gathering, authorised to be carried on by the
                  Medical Officer (Health), or a person designated by the Medical Officer (Health)
                  to give such authorisation.
             (3) During the period referred to in sub-paragraph (1), the operator of a hospital or
      nursing home shall ensure that no person visits a patient in the hospital or nursing home,
      more than once per day, and that each such patient does not have more than one visitor
      per day.
             (4) During the period referred to in sub-paragraph (1), markets shall operate, and
      vending in public arcades and public transportation centres shall take place, only during—
            (a)   the hours of 6:00 am to 2:00 pm on April 8, 2020;
            (b)   the hours of 6:00 am to 7:00 pm on April 9, 2020 (Holy Thursday);
            (c)   the hours of 7:00 am to 2:00 pm on April 11, 2020;
            (d)   the period April 14, 2020 to April 21, 2020—
                        (i)    the hours of 6:00 am to 2:00 pm on Sundays, Mondays, Tuesdays
                               and Wednesdays; and
                        (ii)   the hours of 6:00 am to 6:00 pm on Thursdays, Fridays and
                               Saturdays,
      except that on April 10, 2020 (Good Friday), April 12, 2020 (Easter Sunday) and April 13,
      2020 (Easter Monday), all markets shall remain closed, and no vending shall take place in
      public arcades and public transportation centres.
             (5) During the period from the April 8, 2020, to April 21, 2020, the operator of an
      infirmary shall ensure that—
            (a)   no person visits a patient in the infirmary; and
            (b)   no patient of the infirmary is permitted to go outside the infirmary.
              (6) With effect from April 8, 2020, to May 23, 2020, no new patient shall be admitted
      to an infirmary.

11.—(1) Each person shall remain indoors during the hours from 8:00 pm on April 8, 2020,
      to 6:00 am April 9, 2020.
              (2) During the period from April 14, 2020 to April 22, 2020, commencing at 9:00 pm
      on April 14, 2020, and ending at 5:00 am on April 22, 2020, each person shall remain indoors
      during the hours from 9:00 pm to 5:00 am each day.
              (3) Sub-paragraphs (1) and (2) shall not apply to—
            (a)   members of the Houses of Parliament and persons employed to the Houses of
                  Parliament;
            (b)   Permanent Secretaries, the Solicitor-General and the Chief Parliamentary Counsel;
            (c)   any member of a security force;
            (d)   any person employed in a service concerning the provision of health, water,
                  electricity, public works, sanitation, firefighting, civil aviation or
                  telecommunications;
            (e)   veterinary surgeons, licensed under the Veterinary Act;
            (f)   immigration officers and customs officers;
            (g)   correctional services officers;
            (h)   persons employed in the transportation of agricultural produce or livestock or
                  employed in the poultry industry (including catching crew, poultry processing
                  plant staff and the staff of feed mills);
