           (i)   persons employed in the sugar cane industry;
           (j)   persons employed to “tourist establishments” as defined by the Public Health
                 (Tourist Establishments) Regulations, 2000;
           (k)   persons employed in services connected with oil-refining and with the loading,
                 distribution or transportation of petroleum fuel, liquefied natural gas or any
                 renewable energy source;
           (l)   persons employed in services connected with the loading and unloading of
                 ships and with the storage and delivery of goods at, or from, docks, wharves and
                 warehouses operated in connection with docks or wharves;
           (m)   persons employed in the provision of public transportation by the Jamaica Urban
                 Transit Company or the Montego Bay Metro Company Limited;
           (n)   the Judiciary and persons employed to the courts;
           (o)   persons employed to the business process outsourcing sector;
           (p)   persons employed to the media (such as journalists, television or radio
                 presenters, camera operators, announcers, engineers, technicians and newspaper
                 delivery personnel);
           (q)   persons employed to businesses providing private security;
           (r)   persons employed to the Jamaica Printing Services Limited;
           (s)   persons employed to the Toll Authority established under the Toll Roads Act;
           (t)   persons employed to courier services;
           (u)   persons employed in the bauxite or alumina industries;
           (v)   persons engaged in the transportation of manufactured products;
           (w)   persons employed to Factories as defined in the Factories Act;
           (x)   Mayors and Councillors of Municipal Corporations;
           (y)   persons employed to the Independent Commission of Investigations;
           (z)   persons employed to the Cabinet Office, the Office of the Prime Minister, the
                 Ministry with responsibility for finance and the public service, Tax Administration
                 Jamaica, the Accountant General’s Department or eGov Jamaica Limited;
           (aa) the Director-General of the Office of Disaster Preparedness and Emergency
                Management and persons authorised in writing by the Director-General; and
           (bb) persons employed in any service or activity designated in writing by the Minister
                with responsibility for national security, with the prior approval of the Cabinet,
                as an exempt service or activity under this sub-paragraph,
     for the purposes of that employment, service, activity or authorisation, or duties as such
     member (as the case may be).
