13. During the period from April 8, 2020, to April 21, 2020, when in a public place, each of
     the following persons shall wear a mask fitted to that person’s face so as to cover that
     person’s nose and mouth—
            (a)    a person who has attained the age of 65 years or more;
            (b)    a person who has the “flu” or a respiratory illness;
            (c)    a person who has the care of—
                          (i)     another person who is in quarantine or isolation;
                          (ii)    another person who is suspected or confirmed with SARS – CoV-2
                                  (Coronavirus COVID-19); or
                          (iii)   another person who is exhibiting flu-like symptoms or respiratory
                                  symptoms;
            (d)    a person who has comorbid illnesses.
